1 (b) Notwithstanding Subsection (a) of this section, the County may enter into a
2 contract for solid waste disposal that:
3 (1) May include transportation;
4 (2) May require payment of funds from appropriations of the County or
5 receipt of payment to the County; and
6 (3) Is not for more than a twenty–year initial term.
7 (c) A contract requiring the payment of funds from appropriations of more than
8 one fiscal year, approved by resolution of the Commissioners, shall be awarded as:
9 (1) A one–year contract with the option to renew for not more than four
10 one–year terms for a contract that is not governed by item (2) of this Subsection; or
11 (2) A multiyear contract for a period not to exceed 20 years, including the
12 initial contract term and all options, if the contract is for:
13 (i) Banking and investment services;
14 (ii) Retirement and pension system management;
15 (iii) Health insurance; or
16 (iv) Information technology, including software and the provision of
17 voice, data, and Internet services.
18 (d) (1) Notwithstanding Subsection (a) of this section, the County may enter
19 into [a] THE FOLLOWING CONTRACTS IF THE INITIAL TERM OF THE CONTRACT OR
20 LEASE IS NOT MORE THAN 20 YEARS:
21 (I) A contract for a cellular tower lease, including a cellular tower
22 lease on a water tower[, if the initial term of the lease is not more than 20 years]; AND
23 (II) CONTRACTS FOR INFRASTRUCTURE OR ASSET
24 MANAGEMENT PROGRAMS IF THE INFRASTRUCTURE OR ASSET HAS A LIFE CYCLE OF
25 NOT LESS THAN 15 YEARS, INCLUDING WATER TOWERS, FLOW METERS, AND OTHER
26 WATER AND SEWER ASSETS.
27 (2) A CONTRACT FOR INFRASTRUCTURE OR AN ASSET MANAGEMENT
28 PROGRAM UNDER PARAGRAPH (1)(II) OF THIS SUBSECTION MAY INCLUDE THE
29 PLANNING, DESIGN, CONSTRUCTION, OPERATION, MAINTENANCE, MODIFICATION,
30 REVITALIZATION, AND DECOMMISSIONING OF THE INFRASTRUCTURE OR ASSET.

